Five municipal workers who had fallen into sewage treatment works are believed to have drowned.Kimberley police this afternoon confirmed that they were recovering the bodies of five workers who had fallen into the treatment works in Homestead this morning.Sello Matsie, spokesperson for the Sol Plaatje Municipality, said the municipality could only confirm the incident. We still have to notify the families so we cannot reveal the names of the deceased. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.